column2: Rained for five days straight.  High winds and bloom started on north and east.
Very windy at 15-20 mph and bright sun.
Sunny- very calm- no boats- and saw one loon.
Cloudy- sun- windy at 5-10 mph- not many weeds- and saw an eagle.
Sunny- cool- nice day.  Eight boats on the lake (tournament).
Finally sunny- calm- saw 2 ducks- and 1 loon.
Partly sunny- 1 duck- 1 loon- few lily pads- and weeds starting.
Hot weather- weed growing good- slight chop- sunny- and 1 loon.
Weeds rotting- 1 blue heron- and choppy.
Sunny- light south wind- saw 2 loons- 3 ducks- and 1 eagle.
Sunny- calm bays- light green scum- 7 boats- and geese.
Cloudy and sunny.  5 boats out.  East wind 5-10 mph.  Saw 2 eagles.
Sunny- lite NW wind.  2 boats out.  Saw 2 loons Tues. They lower lake 9"
3 boats out.  Lake water normal.  Lot of bass being caught.
Cloudy- NW wind.  Lake very green-brown (too early).  Lots of bass being caught 9-11.5".
Cloudy- east wind.  Lake turning over.  Saw 6 half grown ducks.  1 eagle.
S wind. Yellow green by shore.  No boats.  Fish jumping for bugs  along shore.
Light clouds.  Calm water.  Saw Ma loon and med chick. Bay is full of yellow-green smelly slime.
Had rained- now sunny.  2 boats out.  South wind.
Real sunny.  2 boats out.  1 blue heron.
Sunny- 5 boats- 2 blue herons- 2 loons and 2 loon chicks.
Sunny- 3 boats- 5 young wood duck- 4 mallards.
Sunny- 3 boats.  12 sea gulls- 2 blue herons.
Sunny- waves.  6 boats.  3 loons.  1 duck and 7 babies.  1 beaver.
Sunny- wavy.  No boats- no birds.
2 loons- 1 eagle and a few ducks.
2 boats- 1 loon and 2 geese with 9 goslings. Sunny with a north wind.
Sunny with a light wind from the south. 3 boats- 2 loons. 1 goose with 5 goslings.
Some clouds. 5 boats. 4 dead crappies by shore.
1 boat- 1 loon and some gulls. 1 boat- 1 loon and some gulls. Partly sunny.
Partly sunny. 3 boats and 2 pontoons. 1 loon.
sunny- 79 degrees. 2 gulls- 3 boats- a canoe- and 2 paddle boats.
sunny- 77 degrees. 1 loon- no boats. Light wind.
sunny- light wind. No boats. 1 loon and 1 gull.
2 boats. 1 goose with 4 chicks. 2 loons- 3 blue herons.
2 boats. 27 geese. Most aquatic plants I have ever seen since I moved here in 1997.
